* chore(resumable-media): remove Python <=3.4 support

* Use a byte template to create multipart payload

With the Python <=3.4 support dropped, byte string templates can be
used, hooray!

* Blacken system tests

* Revert "Use a byte template to create multipart payload"

THis is needed to retain Python 2.7 support for a little longer

* Add back Python 2.7 support

* Add support for Python 3.8
